:QUOTE
A tight community of 200 paying members outperforms a free server of 10,000.

:INFO
Paid Discord Community
A paid Discord community generates recurring revenue while building a high-signal audience around a shared interest or skill. The key is structure, onboarding, and consistent value delivery.

:COUNTER.half
100 Members
First milestone for a sustainable paid community
|
:COUNTER.half
9 USD
Common monthly price point for niche communities

:PATH
Structure Phase
Design the channel architecture before launch. Limit channels to what you can actively moderate. Every channel needs a clear purpose and activity cadence.

:PATH
Launch Phase
Use a waitlist landing page to build anticipation. Launch with a founding member discount available only for the first 30 to 60 days. Create urgency with a clear deadline.

:PATH
Retain Phase
Weekly value drops keep members active: AMAs, resource shares, live sessions, or curated content. Engagement declines fastest in months two and three.

:CHECKLIST
Discord Community Launch Checklist
[ ] Define community focus and member promise
[ ] Design channel structure (under 15 channels at launch)
[ ] Set up Whop or Memberful for payment gating
[ ] Write onboarding message and welcome flow
[ ] Create a community rules and norms document
[ ] Build waitlist landing page
[ ] Set founding member price and deadline
[ ] Plan first four weeks of content and events
[ ] Recruit five seed members before public launch

:NOTE
The welcome experience is the most important moment in member retention. A new member who does not receive a response or take a meaningful action in their first 48 hours is very likely to churn at the next billing cycle.